ved, thus word/word. The separation of entries is indicated on the printed page by extra space between lines; when the end of a manuscript entry coincides with the end of a page of the printed text, the symbol [#] follows the entry. A full discussion of textual procedures accompanies the tables of emendation and details of inscription in the Textual Apparatus at the end of each volume; specific textual problems are explained in headnotes or footnotes when unusual situations warrant.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  a19th century literature.  aamerican author.  aamerican literature.  acasual twain.  aclassics.  aday in the life.  aeveryday twain.  ahannibal.  ahumor.  ajuvenilia.  aliterary criticism.  amarginalia.  amark twain.  amissouri.  anonfiction.  aphrenology.  asamuel clemens.  asatire.  asocial commentary.  atravel writings.  aturn of the century.  atwain drafts.  atwains notebook.  aunpublished twain.1 aAnderson, Frederick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrank, Michael Barry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSanderson, Kenneth M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052090538240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520905382423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520905382/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles